original: Johanson, Johan Wilhelm, disponent, Nässjö, f. 12/9/84 i Vallsjö, Jön-köp. 1., av verkmäst. Anders J. o. Emma Pettersson. G. 14 m. Anna Mar-tell. Barn: Ingrid f. 16, barnträdg:-lär:a Gbg, Margit 20, barnträdg:-lär la, Sthlm, Nil’s 23, jur. stud., Sthlm. — Avg:ex. fr. Norrköpings tekn. elem:sk. 04, stud. i Tyskl. Ing. v. Nässjö Jäst- o. Spritfabr. A-B 08-19, disp. f. Sv. Jästfabr. A-B i Nässjö sed. 19. Led. av styr. f. A-B Kläder-fabr. i Nässjö o. Nässjö Brygg. A-B sed. 22 samt A-B Smål. Banks avd:-kont. Led. av Sv. tekn:fören. sed. 34. RVOllkl.
translated: Johanson, Johan Wilhelm, manager, Nässjö, b. 9/12/84 in Vallsjö, Jönköping County, son of foreman Anders J. and Emma Pettersson. Married in 1914 to Anna Martell. Children: Ingrid, b. 1916, preschool teacher in Gothenburg; Margit, b. 1920, preschool teacher in Stockholm; Nils, b. 1923, studying law in Stockholm. Johanson graduated from Norrköping Technical School in 1904 and studied engineering in Germany. He worked at Nässjö Yeast and Spirit Factory from 1908-1919, and has been employed as a manager at Swedish Yeast Factory AB in Nässjö since 1919. He is a board member of AB Kläderfabriken and Nässjö Bryggeri AB since 1922, and of the Smalland Bank's department since 1934. Johanson has received the Royal Order of Vasa.
